00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:17.830
that many which are
raised in the proceeding.

00:14:17.830 --> 00:14:20.270
So part of it's that, and part of
it is do you have the same rules

00:14:20.270 --> 00:14:21.760
for every sector of the economy.

00:14:21.760 --> 00:14:25.240
Is it the same thing for movies as
it is for auto parts, for example,

00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:26.960
which will be discussed here?

00:14:26.960 --> 00:14:29.700
Is it the same thing
for textbooks as it is

00:14:29.700 --> 00:14:31.080
for computer games and things?

00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:33.880
And I think it's a mistake
to have a unitary system

00:14:33.880 --> 00:14:35.380
where everything is
kind of thrown together.

00:14:35.380 --> 00:14:40.470
So I think part of the way forward
is to recognize that not all uses

00:14:40.470 --> 00:14:42.400
of goods present the same problems.

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:44.360
Part of the solution is to--

00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:50.280
is to realize that there should
be some affirmative obligations

00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:53.250
on people that expect legal
protection in the state to,

00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:56.070
you know, help enforce their
technical protection measures

00:14:56.070 --> 00:14:58.100 position:56%
to address public interest in areas.

00:14:58.100 --> 00:15:04.450
And I think the other area is it
may be that there's more of a realm

00:15:04.450 --> 00:15:08.160
for a category of people
that are authorized

00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:12.610
to use circumvention devices
under certain contexts.

00:15:12.610 --> 00:15:14.890
For example, in the
area for blind people,

00:15:14.890 --> 00:15:16.190
it's great that blind
people have the,

00:15:16.190 --> 00:15:19.420
you know, the right to circumvent.

00:15:19.420 --> 00:15:22.730
But I mean, it's not something
that all blind people can do

00:15:22.730 --> 00:15:27.910
without depending on someone
to provide a service for them.

00:15:27.910 --> 00:15:30.040
Same thing I'm sure is for
people that want to, you know,

00:15:30.040 --> 00:15:31.810
fix their own cars or
something like that.

00:15:31.810 --> 00:15:35.660
Not everybody can do
these things on their own.

00:15:35.660 --> 00:15:40.560
But it may be that you-- in some
areas, you may feel like you want

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:43.640
to have some-- not completely
open the door all the way,

00:15:43.640 --> 00:15:47.120
but you may want to have some
some sense that the people

00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:50.250
that are authorized
to provide services

00:15:50.250 --> 00:15:52.270
like that are somehow
more accountable

00:15:52.270 --> 00:15:54.670
and following some more
circumspect things.

00:15:54.670 --> 00:15:57.110
And so I think just in
terms of opening things,

00:15:57.110 --> 00:15:59.330
that's what I wanted to say.

00:15:59.330 --> 00:16:00.630
&gt;&gt; Regan Smith: OK.

