00:17:15.550 --> 00:17:16.850
&gt;&gt; Regan Smith: Thank you.

00:17:16.850 --> 00:17:18.150
Ms. Besek?

00:17:18.150 --> 00:17:19.850
Excuse me?

00:17:19.850 --> 00:17:24.610
&gt;&gt; June Besek: It didn't
go all the way.

00:17:24.610 --> 00:17:29.330
So I guess I'm not as
certain as Mr. Love is

00:17:29.330 --> 00:17:33.630
about how you can make these
discriminations between content,

00:17:33.630 --> 00:17:39.280
because I think that educators and
librarians would say that movies

00:17:39.280 --> 00:17:42.340
and other kinds of works
are very relevant--

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:43.700
you know, music and
things like that.

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:45.740
So I think one of the difficulties

00:17:45.740 --> 00:17:48.190
that we all face is
