or white, an either/or.

00:18:36.530 --> 00:18:41.470
You can't argue that a
system isn't effective just

00:18:41.470 --> 00:18:44.050
because some people can bypass.

00:18:44.050 --> 00:18:46.660
There's always been some
degree of infringement.

00:18:46.660 --> 00:18:48.120
There always will be.

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:50.180
The real goal is to
reduce it to the level

00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:52.230
where you still have
a viable market.

00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:55.090
So that-- I think that goes back
to Keith's comment about, you know,

00:18:55.090 --> 00:18:57.680
you don't want it just
available at Best Buy.

00:18:57.680 --> 00:18:59.040
Well, you don't want
it just available--

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:02.060
I was thinking of Walmart,
actually Keith, but the same idea.

00:19:02.060 --> 00:19:05.360
And so, it's really important
that that material not be--

00:19:05.360 --> 00:19:09.560
you know, the circumvention means
not be so generally available.

00:19:09.560 --> 00:19:12.270 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Regan Smith: So you would agree
to keep it out of Walmart, Best Buy,

00:19:12.270 --> 00:19:15.910
sort of the easy access to
the law-abiding citizens

00:19:15.910 --> 00:19:18.570
and the hackers can find
things in the dark corners

00:19:18.570 --> 00:19:21.180
and that's not proof
