01:13:03.290 --> 01:13:06.570
to conclude that this
is a lawful activity

01:13:06.570 --> 01:13:09.520
that is being petitioned for.

01:13:09.520 --> 01:13:14.950
So why is it necessary,
again rhetorically--

01:13:14.950 --> 01:13:20.170
is it necessary to look down the
page to (a)(2) and (b)(1) and say,

01:13:20.170 --> 01:13:25.480
oh my gosh, if we grant
this petition in the terms

01:13:25.480 --> 01:13:30.960
for which it's been petitioned for,
so as to-- however you phrase it--

01:13:30.960 --> 01:13:36.840
allow some expert assistance in
the form of a service or, you know,

01:13:36.840 --> 01:13:43.770 position:56%
somebody's aftermarket product or
software, no court is going to say--

01:13:43.770 --> 01:13:49.480
because they can read the law too--
that, oh my gosh, we're not going

01:13:49.480 --> 01:13:56.130 position:56%
to allow this case against a
trafficker to proceed under the DMCA

01:13:56.130 --> 01:14:00.000
because the Copyright
Office granted an exemption

01:14:00.000 --> 01:14:02.850
to a user who had a lawful right.

01:14:02.850 --> 01:14:08.610
I mean, respectfully, I don't agree
that the law should be interpreted

01:14:08.610 --> 01:14:13.190
to take that power away
from the Copyright Office.

01:14:13.190 --> 01:14:18.590
The NTIA didn't think so
in its recommendations.

01:14:18.590 --> 01:14:22.000
At least our reading of
the legislative history,

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:24.800
when you read all of the
legislative history at the time

01:14:24.800 --> 01:14:29.360
that this was presented to the
Congress in terms of black boxes

01:14:29.360 --> 01:14:34.670
and for one purpose and not wanting
to interfere with interoperability

01:14:34.670 --> 01:14:40.820
or the legitimate activities
of retailers and servicers.

01:14:40.820 --> 01:14:46.400
So again, back to your question
of what evidence is necessary,

01:14:46.400 --> 01:14:49.540
once you've concluded that
the activity is lawful

01:14:49.540 --> 01:14:52.090
and you've concluded that
it doesn't involve copying

01:14:52.090 --> 01:14:57.240
of expressive content, if you still
need to look for any evidence,

01:14:57.240 --> 01:15:00.420
if you're worried about
trafficking, then look to those

01:15:00.420 --> 01:15:04.120
who oppose the exemption
to provide such evidence.

01:15:04.120 --> 01:15:07.610
Otherwise, there should be a
presumption under the power

01:15:07.610 --> 01:15:12.620
that you already have that it
includes the right to expert help,

01:15:12.620 --> 01:15:16.620
just as it was silently
assumed in the case of phones,

01:15:16.620 --> 01:15:19.110
or else nobody would have
ever gotten the benefit

01:15:19.110 --> 01:15:20.690
of those exemptions.

01:15:20.690 --> 01:15:23.470
&gt;&gt; Kevin Amer: Thank you.

01:15:23.470 --> 01:15:26.530
&gt;&gt; Andrew Moore: So turning--
Sorry, turning away a little bit

01:15:26.530 --> 01:15:27.870
